# Code owners — auto-requests maintainer review on PRs touching sensitive
# paths (launch-readiness §B). The security boundary and the surfaces that
# construct the container launch are the load-bearing files; a change there
# should never merge without an explicit maintainer look.
#
# Syntax: <path-pattern> <@owner>. Last matching pattern wins.

# Default: everything is maintainer-reviewed until co-maintainers exist.
*                       @BuckG71

# Security-critical surfaces — called out explicitly so they stay owned
# even if the default above is later relaxed to a team.
/whizzard/safety.py     @BuckG71
/whizzard/docker_cmd.py @BuckG71
/whizzard/mounts.py     @BuckG71
/whizzard/requests.py   @BuckG71
/whizzard/adapters/     @BuckG71
/.github/               @BuckG71
/whizzard/_dockerfiles/ @BuckG71
